# Getting started with Google Cloud Vision

To use any of the above modules, you need to connect your Google account to the Google Cloud Vision project and to Integromat. If you do not have a Google account yet, you can create one at [cloud.google.com/vision](https://cloud.google.com/vision/).

## Connecting a Google account to the Google Cloud Vision service

To connect your Google account to Google Cloud Vision, visit the [cloud.google.com/vision](https://cloud.google.com/vision/) and sign in using your Google account. 

To configure your project properly for connecting to Integromat, you need to prepare and understand the project properly.

You can follow the instructions [before-you-begin](https://cloud.google.com/vision/docs/before-you-begin/), or read steps in this guide.

## Overview

Read the overview [quickstart](https://cloud.google.com/vision/docs/quickstart/) to understand the Google Cloud Vision properly.

## Managing your project

Go to the console by clicking the **Console** button and choose your project in the top menu. Or you can create a new project.

See [creating-managing-projects](https://cloud.google.com/resource-manager/docs/) for more details.

### Enabling the Cloud Vision API

Continue to the **Navigation menu** by clicking the list icon in the left corner and click the tab **Library**.

Find **Cloud Vision API** and manage this API to be enabled.

Or enable this API through the instruction written here [before-you-begin](https://cloud.google.com/vision/docs/before-you-begin) by clicking **ENABLE API**.

### Linking a Billing account

Continue to the **Navigation menu** by clicking the list icon in the left corner and click the tab **Billing**.

Assign a billing account by linking an existing billing account or by creating a new billing account.

See [manage-billing-account](https://cloud.google.com/billing/docs/how-to/manage-billing-account/) for more details.

## Connecting the Google Cloud Vision service to Integromat

To connect your Google Cloud Vision project to Integromat, follow the general instructions for [Connecting to services](https://support.integromat.com/hc/en-us/articles/360001990194#create-a-connection).

When creating a connection, you will be requested to enter your API Key. To get the API key, log into your Google Cloud Vision project and follow the instructions for getting the API key.

Once you have copied the displayed API token and pasted it in Integromat, you can continue and finish your scenario.

## Getting the API key

Continue to the **Navigation menu** by clicking the list icon in the left corner and click the tab **APIs & Services**. Then click the tab **Credentials**.

Select **Create credentials**, then select API key from the dropdown menu.

Click the **Create** button. The API key created dialog box displays your newly created key.

See [getting-api-key](https://cloud.google.com/docs/authentication/api-keys?hl=en&visit_id=636729666965680236-2433506166&rd=1) for more details.
